<TITLE> President, CA greet nation on Eid </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 8 (bdnews24.com)  President Iajuddin Ahmed and chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed in separate messages greeted the nation on the eve of Eid-ul-Azha on Tuesday. In his message, the president said, "On the occasion of the Eid-Ul-Azha, I congratulate the people of the country as well as the Muslim community." He said Hazrat Ibrahim's devotion, love and sacrifice to Allah, proven by his readiness to give up his dearest son Hazrat Ismail, was unprecedented. "Ibrahim's such devotion, love and sacrifice for almighty Allah is very essential to reflect in our personal and social life." The sacrifice of Eid-ul-Azha will tighten further the solidarity of Muslim community, the president said. Fakhruddin said, "May the holy Eid-ul-Azha bring happiness, prosperity and welfare in our life." He said the unprecedented sacrifice of Hazrat Ibhrahim is worthy of being followed. The chief adviser called on the people to be united regardless nation, religion or cast to work in establishing a peaceful, welfare state.
